      FAQs

      How do I clean the cutting board?

      Just rinse with warm water and soap - that’s it. The non-porous surface repels stains and bacteria, so it never holds onto smells or food residue. It’s also dishwasher-safe.

      Can I use it for both meat and vegetables?

      Absolutely! The non-porous surface won’t absorb juices, odors, or bacteria like wood or plastic can. Just make sure to rinse or wipe between uses if you’re switching from raw meat to vegetables, as proper cleaning is still important to avoid cross-contamination.

      Will this dull my knives over time?

      Like all cutting surfaces, some wear on your knife edge is expected over time - even with wood or plastic. The Titan Pro preserves your blade much better than glass, ceramic, or stone boards that can ruin knives quickly. While it’s slightly harder than plastic or wood, it won’t destroy your blades - and with regular honing or sharpening (like most chefs recommend), your knives will stay in great shape.

      Does it come with a warranty?

      Yes, all Titan Pro boards come with a free 1-Year durability guarantee. If anything happens due to a manufacturing fault, we’ll replace it free.

      Is it heavy or hard to handle?

      Not at all. Despite being solid metal, the board is surprisingly lightweight and easy to move, thanks to its sleek profile and handle cutout.

      How is this better than wood or plastic boards?

      The Titan Pro doesn’t absorb bacteria, crack, stain, or wear down. Absolutely no warping, no plastic toxins and no bascteria. It’s built to outlast every other board in your kitchen, and look cleaner doing it.
